knowledge_graph.title: Dumpling
knowledge_graph.description: Dumpling is a broad class of dishes that consist of pieces of cooked dough, often wrapped around a filling. The dough can be based on bread, wheat or other flours, or potatoes, and it may be filled with meat, fish, tofu, cheese, vegetables, or a combination.

related_questions.question: What are dumplings made out of?
related_questions.snippet: Dumplings are most commonly formed from flour or meal bound with egg and then simmered in water or gravy stock until they take on a light cakey texture. Many recipes call for herbs, onions, grated cheese, or chopped meat to be rolled into the dough before cooking.
related_questions.title: Dumpling | Definition, Types, & Ingredients - Britannica

related_questions.question: Are dumplings Chinese or Japanese?
related_questions.snippet: Originating in China, the dumpling, more commonly called the potsticker, is made of wheat flour dough wrapper filled with meat and/or vegetables. This common side dish is cooked many different ways. Dumplings are most commonly steamed, pan fried, deep fried, or boiled.
related_questions.title: The Difference Between Dumplings And Gyoza

related_questions.question: What is the definition of a dumpling?
related_questions.snippet: : a small mass of dough cooked by boiling or steaming. chicken soup with dumplings. b. : a casing of dough enclosing a typically savory filling (such as meat or seafood) and cooked usually by boiling, steaming, or pan-frying see gyoza, pot sticker, wonton.
related_questions.title: Dumpling Definition & Meaning - Merriam-Webster

related_questions.question: What is the American version of dumplings?
related_questions.snippet: Originating in the Pennsylvania region the pierogies have been a staple in the city of Pittsburgh and all over western Pennsylvania. Pierogies are soft semicircular dumplings that are usually filled with potatoes or cheese. However, just like other dumplings, fillings are interchangeable depending on culture.
